WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:15.015
After the first two suspects. a third man
entered and locked the doors. right?

2
00:00:15.098 --> 00:00:17.225
{\an8}-Yeah.
-[Stiles] What happened next. Mr. Wilson?

3
00:00:17.308 --> 00:00:19.477
{\an8}He put a fucking gun to my head.

4
00:00:19.561 --> 00:00:22.147
{\an8}-I-- I had no choice.
-[dramatic music playing]

5
00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:27.610
{\an8}I opened the safe. The store owners
don't pay us enough for this bullshit.

6
00:00:27.694 --> 00:00:30.780
Mariela and Elena will back me up.

7
00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:34.451
-Wait. You work with the other managers?
-[Wilson] Mm-hm.

8
00:00:34.534 --> 00:00:37.328
So all three stores
are owned by the same people.

9
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:40.206
Lenn and Paulina Petri
own all three stores.

10
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:42.500
And we all have the same security system.

11
00:00:43.084 --> 00:00:46.629
That man. he hit the alarm.
and he told me to open the safe.

12
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.381
But my hands were shaking.

13
00:00:48.965 --> 00:00:52.802
I-I was trying to go fast.
but I was so scared.

14
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:56.765
He got close to my ear. and he said…

15
00:00:56.848 --> 00:00:59.976
<i>-"Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast."</i>
-Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast.

16
00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:01.770
[intriguing music playing]

17
00:01:02.353 --> 00:01:04.689
[Stiles] Now. who else spoke to you
during the robbery?

18
00:01:06.232 --> 00:01:07.567
[exhales]

19
00:01:07.650 --> 00:01:08.693
[Jormond] The crazy one.

20
00:01:08.777 --> 00:01:11.488
He started yelling. "10.000 I do. cuh."

21
00:01:11.571 --> 00:01:13.448
"On the set. Who wanna bet?"

22
00:01:13.531 --> 00:01:17.160
Crazy-ass wanted us to gamble on
when he blew up that damn wall.

23
00:01:18.203 --> 00:01:19.704
But he knew what he was doing. though.

24
00:01:19.788 --> 00:01:21.998
He had no problem
setting up that bomb shit.

25
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.918
Like he'd done it before.

26
00:01:25.001 --> 00:01:27.003
[cell phone buzzing]

27
00:01:31.508 --> 00:01:34.260
-[Stiles] I should've rescheduled this.
-[Cruz] You love Candace. right?

28
00:01:34.344 --> 00:01:36.596
Of course I love Candace.
but I also love my job.

29
00:01:36.679 --> 00:01:39.099
I love my job too. and I'm divorced.

30
00:01:39.182 --> 00:01:42.143
Thanks to joint custody.
I won't even see my son for Thanksgiving.

31
00:01:42.644 --> 00:01:45.897
I'm your cautionary tale. bro.
The ghost of Thanksgiving future.

32
00:01:45.980 --> 00:01:48.108
-For real. Stiles.
-I gotta go.

33
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.444
-[camera shutter clicking]
-[ominous music playing]

34
00:01:51.528 --> 00:01:53.446
Tell Candace I said hi.

35
00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:56.533
[Stiles] Don't brief Sealey
till I get back. All right?

36
00:01:58.743 --> 00:02:01.371
[suspenseful music playing]

37
00:02:01.454 --> 00:02:02.539
[Stiles] I'm here. I'm here.

38
00:02:03.581 --> 00:02:05.583
I know. I hit traffic.

39
00:02:06.751 --> 00:02:08.169
What's up. man?

40
00:02:08.253 --> 00:02:13.967
Isaiah. what happened?
Candace says you left Noah on the street?

41
00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:17.887
Nah. I had my radio off. But when we saw
the cruiser zoom past the restaurant.

42
00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:19.722
Noah wanted to know what was going on.

43
00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:21.850
You're seriously blaming Noah
for what you did?

44
00:02:21.933 --> 00:02:24.853
I'm not blaming anybody. Candace.
I'm stating the facts.

45
00:02:24.936 --> 00:02:27.105
Dad's right. I did ask him.

46
00:02:27.188 --> 00:02:30.024
I wouldn't have heard the call-out
if you hadn't asked. I mean--

47
00:02:30.108 --> 00:02:32.152
What was I supposed to do?
I called him an Uber.

48
00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:33.862
Take him to an active crime scene?

49
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:37.740
You were supposed to eat lunch
with your son and bring him home. but--

50
00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:38.783
[Wade] Candace.

51
00:02:38.867 --> 00:02:41.244
Can we ask Noah how he feels?

52
00:02:41.327 --> 00:02:42.328
[sighs]

53
00:02:43.746 --> 00:02:44.581
Yes.

54
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:46.958
I wanted to hang out with you.

55
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.752
And you just booked it.

56
00:02:51.629 --> 00:02:55.967
Okay. so what can your father do
to make it up to you?

57
00:02:58.928 --> 00:03:00.180
I wanna see my grandfather.

58
00:03:01.097 --> 00:03:01.931
No.

59
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:04.309
Noah. no. No.

60
00:03:04.392 --> 00:03:05.727
It's not gonna happen.

61
00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:07.228
I see Amos. That's it.

62
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:12.317
If you want to maintain your boundary.
why not compromise?

63
00:03:12.817 --> 00:03:14.569
Take Noah to see him.

64
00:03:14.652 --> 00:03:16.321
Supervise them.

65
00:03:22.118 --> 00:03:23.161
Fine.

66
00:03:23.745 --> 00:03:24.579
[Wade] Great.

67
00:03:25.121 --> 00:03:28.875
Noah. could you give me a few minutes
to talk with your parents alone?

68
00:03:28.958 --> 00:03:29.959
Yes. ma'am.

69
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:31.461
Thank you.

70
00:03:33.421 --> 00:03:34.505
[Candace scoffs]

71
00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:39.135
Now that we have addressed Noah's needs.

72
00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:43.973
Candace. what do you need from Isaiah?

73
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:48.645
I need to feel like…
he's showing up for me.

74
00:03:49.187 --> 00:03:50.939
Like we're on the same team.

75
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.107
Like we used to be.

76
00:03:54.067 --> 00:03:57.612
And what does that look like for you?
Be specific.

77
00:04:02.075 --> 00:04:05.995
I want Isaiah to attend
the Baldwin Hills Cares Gala with me.

78
00:04:06.829 --> 00:04:08.539
But he needs to leave work at work.

79
00:04:08.623 --> 00:04:10.333
No phone. no interruptions.

80
00:04:10.416 --> 00:04:13.544
My job does not work that way.
I'm always on call. baby.

81
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:15.964
This gala is really important
to me. Isaiah.

82
00:04:16.047 --> 00:04:20.551
I know it's not police work.
but it's my contribution to our community.

83
00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:22.679
-The gala. it's honoring--
-Fine.

84
00:04:24.472 --> 00:04:25.765
I'll go.

85
00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:28.810
No phone.

86
00:04:30.436 --> 00:04:31.729
And. Isaiah.

87
00:04:33.189 --> 00:04:35.692
what do you need from Candace in return?

88
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:41.030
[pensive music playing]

89
00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:42.740
I need…

90
00:04:44.158 --> 00:04:48.997
to move back into my house
and sleep in my bed next to my wife.

91
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:50.206
[Candace exhales]

92
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.542
Candace. I understand your reluctance.

93
00:04:53.876 --> 00:04:55.503
But Isaiah is trying.

94
00:04:55.586 --> 00:04:56.838
And so am I.

95
00:04:57.630 --> 00:05:00.591
And Isaiah's saying
that he'll attend the gala.

96
00:05:00.675 --> 00:05:02.093
It is a step in the right direction.

97
00:05:02.176 --> 00:05:04.095
but he needs to follow through
with his actions.

98
00:05:05.221 --> 00:05:08.391
And then we can talk
about him moving back in.

99
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:12.145
And ending the separation.

100
00:05:12.228 --> 00:05:14.230
[music fades out]

101
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:18.401
["On Your Face" playing]

102
00:05:21.571 --> 00:05:25.908
<i>♪ Ah. ooh-ah-ooh-ah. ooh-ah-oh… ♪</i>

103
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:26.868
[Coltrane] My man.

104
00:05:26.951 --> 00:05:28.494
[man] Good morning. Mr. Wilder.

105
00:05:28.578 --> 00:05:31.080
<i>♪ Shows on your face ♪</i>

106
00:05:31.164 --> 00:05:34.083
<i>♪ And no matter how you try to hide… ♪</i>

107
00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:35.335
[Coltrane] Hey. sis.

108
00:05:35.418 --> 00:05:36.336
Ella.

109
00:05:36.961 --> 00:05:39.756
Can we keep this short?
I have a class to teach in 30 minutes.

110
00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:42.342
Come into my office. please. Hey.

111
00:05:44.052 --> 00:05:47.055
You know. as much as I appreciate
you paying Kyra's tuition.

112
00:05:47.138 --> 00:05:49.349
you normally just put it in the mail.

113
00:05:49.432 --> 00:05:50.808
I wanted to see you.

114
00:05:51.309 --> 00:05:53.770
<i>♪ Our luck run out</i>
<i>And the wind won't blow… ♪</i>

115
00:05:53.853 --> 00:05:55.063
Hi.

116
00:05:55.146 --> 00:05:56.689
-[Coltrane] Good morning.
-Good morning.

117
00:05:56.773 --> 00:05:58.775
[song fades]

118
00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:03.571
So you in trouble? Is that why
you wanted to talk to me in person?

119
00:06:03.654 --> 00:06:06.115
I'm not in trouble. I'm not.

120
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:10.912
I only. uh. wanted to ask if you and Kyra
are coming to Thanksgiving.

121
00:06:10.995 --> 00:06:12.789
That's a text or a phone call.

122
00:06:12.872 --> 00:06:16.167
-You sure you don't need an alibi?
-Seriously?

123
00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:19.545
I haven't needed an alibi in years.
I've changed. Ella.

124
00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:20.755
[Ella scoffs]

125
00:06:20.838 --> 00:06:22.965
In fact. I'm this close to getting out.

126
00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:27.178
Mmm. That's what Daddy always said.
Then he got himself arrested.

127
00:06:27.261 --> 00:06:29.180
Look around. Ella.

128
00:06:29.263 --> 00:06:30.348
I'm not Daddy.

129
00:06:31.557 --> 00:06:33.476
This is bullshit. 'Trane.

130
00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:35.561
At least he was honest
about being a thief.

131
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:39.190
You still carry around his journal
like a preacher carries a Bible.

132
00:06:39.273 --> 00:06:41.442
-You still mad he left it to me?
-Please.

133
00:06:41.526 --> 00:06:45.029
I wish I could forget his sayings.
his philosophies.

134
00:06:45.113 --> 00:06:48.157
Nah. that journal is in the right hands.

135
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:50.660
I fell into a bottle
because of what's written in there.

136
00:06:50.743 --> 00:06:53.413
while you happily drank the Kool-Aid.

137
00:06:53.496 --> 00:06:56.124
I know how you really make your money.

138
00:06:57.166 --> 00:06:59.252
My part is. I take it anyway.

139
00:07:03.214 --> 00:07:04.632
[Coltrane clears throat]

140
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:11.514
Look. uh.

141
00:07:12.765 --> 00:07:16.811
there may be a small chance that police
may approach you with questions about me.

142
00:07:16.894 --> 00:07:17.728
And there it is.

143
00:07:17.812 --> 00:07:19.105
-I said a very small--
-Don't.

144
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:21.899
Don't worry about it.

145
00:07:21.983 --> 00:07:24.527
Daddy taught me better
than to say shit to the police.

146
00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:26.154
[tense music playing]

147
00:07:26.237 --> 00:07:29.240
Now. how does Ebony feel
about the cops sniffing around?

148
00:07:29.323 --> 00:07:31.284
She doesn't know.
She doesn't need to know.

149
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.745
Ebony hasn't been
the same person since Zahir.

150
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:36.747
If you'd bother to visit her
after we lost him.

151
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:38.040
you would already know that.

152
00:07:41.377 --> 00:07:42.920
Here's your money.

153
00:07:50.261 --> 00:07:51.304
[sighs]

154
00:07:51.929 --> 00:07:53.264
Goodbye. Coltrane.

155
00:07:57.143 --> 00:07:59.687
Coltrane says not to worry. He's got it.

156
00:07:59.770 --> 00:08:01.606
He's got it.
but they were all over the news?

157
00:08:01.689 --> 00:08:02.523
[scoffs]

158
00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:05.026
He better say they shot those guards
'cause they had to.

159
00:08:05.109 --> 00:08:06.402
They had to.

160
00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:10.448
Say more.

161
00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:15.620
I'm telling you this as my sister
and because I'm concerned.

162
00:08:15.703 --> 00:08:17.914
but you cannot tell Coltrane
that we talked.

163
00:08:20.333 --> 00:08:21.250
So.

164
00:08:21.834 --> 00:08:25.087
he told you about Deon stealing the watch
from the Halloween job. right?

165
00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:27.173
[ominous music playing]

166
00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:30.426
I wasn't thrilled. to say the least.

167
00:08:31.719 --> 00:08:34.639
Well. 'Trane said
that Deon got distracted.

168
00:08:34.722 --> 00:08:37.975
and that's what gave the security guards
time to pull their weapons.

169
00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:40.186
At that point.
the crew didn't have a choice.

170
00:08:42.146 --> 00:08:44.273
And what's Coltrane gonna do about Deon?

171
00:08:44.357 --> 00:08:48.569
[exhales] I don't know. Whatever he does.
it's gotta keep him safe at home with me.

172
00:08:50.363 --> 00:08:52.073
You're not gonna
say anything to him. right?

173
00:08:52.156 --> 00:08:53.407
Not a word.

174
00:08:58.496 --> 00:08:59.455
I gotta go.

175
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:02.083
I gotta write up a menu
for my charity gala.

176
00:09:02.583 --> 00:09:05.461
-I'll call you later.
-Okay. Bye.

177
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:08.548
[tense music playing]

178
00:09:09.507 --> 00:09:11.300
[door opens. closes]

179
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:12.510
[sighs]

180
00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:17.014
[line dialing]

181
00:09:17.098 --> 00:09:19.684
-[Tanya] <i>Hello?</i>
-Tanya. Yeah. you talk to Bianca?

182
00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:21.060
She make it out of town?

183
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:25.606
Did you notice anything specific
about the suspects. Miss Douglas?

184
00:09:25.690 --> 00:09:28.985
Yeah. I noticed when they shot the guy
with the gun and the security guard.

185
00:09:29.068 --> 00:09:30.611
I almost fucking shat myself.

186
00:09:31.862 --> 00:09:33.447
I told you. I didn't see anything.

187
00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:35.533
They had their faces covered.

188
00:09:35.616 --> 00:09:37.285
They went in the back
with the manager lady.

189
00:09:37.368 --> 00:09:39.787
they shot the security guys. and ran.

190
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.831
[tense music playing]

191
00:09:41.914 --> 00:09:45.376
How did you know she was a manager?
She said they didn't ask.

192
00:09:45.459 --> 00:09:48.504
They blew up the wall and went to her.
Like they already knew who she was.

193
00:09:51.299 --> 00:09:53.134
I've been to the store before.

194
00:09:53.217 --> 00:09:54.176
When?

195
00:09:55.177 --> 00:09:57.805
Why are you wasting my time
asking these questions?

196
00:09:57.888 --> 00:09:59.890
Obviously. I didn't take anything.

197
00:09:59.974 --> 00:10:01.601
Can I go now?

198
00:10:05.521 --> 00:10:07.231
Sign your statement and go.

199
00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:15.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

200
00:10:16.949 --> 00:10:19.744
[door opens. closes]

201
00:10:20.244 --> 00:10:23.331
[indistinct chatter]

202
00:10:23.414 --> 00:10:24.957
-What's up?
-Hey.

203
00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:26.250
How'd it go?

204
00:10:26.917 --> 00:10:27.918
Uh…

205
00:10:28.002 --> 00:10:30.129
Gotta go to some
fucking adult prom bullshit.

206
00:10:30.212 --> 00:10:31.714
and Noah wants to see my dad.

207
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:34.425
And then maybe
I can move back into my house.

208
00:10:34.508 --> 00:10:36.052
where I pay the mortgage.

209
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:39.722
I might have some good news. A lead.

210
00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:41.349
Here. see?

211
00:10:41.932 --> 00:10:45.102
Bianca Douglas is looking at the officers.
not the perp. like everyone else.

212
00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:46.687
I think we should talk to her again.

213
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:49.065
That guy was running point
with the store managers.

214
00:10:49.148 --> 00:10:51.400
He looks about six feet.

215
00:10:51.942 --> 00:10:54.695
"Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast."

216
00:10:55.321 --> 00:10:56.155
You see that?

217
00:10:56.238 --> 00:10:59.992
That perp was clocking the TV.
Is that sports news?

218
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:05.081
He set explosives on the wall and asked
if anyone wanted to place bets on it.

219
00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:06.749
You think there's a connection to the TV?

220
00:11:06.832 --> 00:11:08.292
-He got distracted by it.
-Stiles.

221
00:11:08.376 --> 00:11:10.086
Are you listening to me?

222
00:11:10.169 --> 00:11:11.921
Did you see Bianca?

223
00:11:12.004 --> 00:11:14.131
She warned them he had a gun.

224
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:16.759
-I think she could be a plant.
-Footage alone won't prove that.

225
00:11:16.842 --> 00:11:20.930
Okay. Well. Bianca left her prints
on her statement form. so I ran them.

226
00:11:21.013 --> 00:11:22.348
Meet Anna Kate Walachek.

227
00:11:22.431 --> 00:11:23.265
Solicitation.

228
00:11:23.349 --> 00:11:25.851
Possession. Possession with intent.
Solicitation again.

229
00:11:25.935 --> 00:11:28.437
Now. three years ago.
she changed her name to Bianca Douglas.

230
00:11:28.521 --> 00:11:30.439
and miraculously. turned clean overnight.

231
00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:31.357
Bullshit.

232
00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:34.276
-You think she's part of the crew?
-I think we need to find out.

233
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:37.947
[Sealey] I know. Fred. I know.
I'm on top of it.

234
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:40.908
Goddamn it. Stiles!

235
00:11:40.991 --> 00:11:43.619
The deputy chief wants me
to wrap this case up quick.

236
00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:45.579
thanks to that little
press conference of yours.

237
00:11:45.663 --> 00:11:48.249
I can do that. but I need resources.

238
00:11:48.332 --> 00:11:49.917
A task force.

239
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.211
-I want the Halloween case.
-Not this shit again!

240
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:53.462
Hear me out.

241
00:11:53.963 --> 00:11:57.675
Cruz thinks there was a woman helping
the perps from inside the jewelry stores.

242
00:11:57.758 --> 00:12:00.553
I looked at the footage
you gave me from Halloween.

243
00:12:01.262 --> 00:12:04.682
Did you notice that there's
five full minutes missing? Did Viggiano?

244
00:12:04.765 --> 00:12:09.145
The security cameras clicked off at 11:47
and came back on at 11:52.

245
00:12:09.228 --> 00:12:11.856
But before that.
our watch complainant. Harvey Swanson…

246
00:12:11.939 --> 00:12:12.773
Mm-hmm.

247
00:12:12.857 --> 00:12:15.317
…isn't anywhere on that footage
for a full 45 minutes.

248
00:12:15.901 --> 00:12:17.403
The last time we see him is here.

249
00:12:21.157 --> 00:12:22.616
Where are they going?

250
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:25.786
At this point in the evening.
Harvey's still wearing his Patek.

251
00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:27.705
The one from the police report.

252
00:12:27.788 --> 00:12:31.333
-And this woman. look at her hand.
-[Cruz] Gotta be five carats. easy.

253
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:33.252
If the robbery happened
while cameras were down.

254
00:12:33.335 --> 00:12:35.546
it happened while Harvey and his friends
were in the room.

255
00:12:35.629 --> 00:12:37.423
And if they took Harvey's watch…

256
00:12:37.506 --> 00:12:40.801
-They took that girl's ring.
-Except we have no police report.

257
00:12:40.885 --> 00:12:43.679
No statement from her.
And I looked through Viggiano's notes.

258
00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.931
She wasn't even there
when Harvey gave his statement.

259
00:12:46.015 --> 00:12:50.186
You're telling me her engagement ring
was stolen. and she didn't even report it?

260
00:12:50.978 --> 00:12:54.064
-Why would she just disappear like that?
-Because she's a plant too.

261
00:12:55.065 --> 00:12:58.652
I told you. It's not the targets
that's the same. it's the method.

262
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:00.446
If you're wrong. it's a waste of time.

263
00:13:00.529 --> 00:13:04.074
If I'm right. it gives us a better shot
at closing both investigations.

264
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:08.162
You get that deputy chief off your ass.
and you get to retire in style. Mm?

265
00:13:10.664 --> 00:13:11.999
[exhales]

266
00:13:12.082 --> 00:13:15.753
All right. for the task force.
I want Mitchell.

267
00:13:15.836 --> 00:13:17.379
-Uribe.
-Washington.

268
00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:19.048
I pick the task force.

269
00:13:19.840 --> 00:13:22.718
If you want the Halloween case.
you keep Viggiano and Harper…

270
00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:25.137
-Fuck Viggiano.
-My squad. my rules.

271
00:13:28.307 --> 00:13:30.643
-Get the fuck out!
-[Stiles] Yes. sir. Yes. sir.

272
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:35.815
So you had
over 100 rich motherfuckers in this place.

273
00:13:35.898 --> 00:13:37.525
and you're the only person
that got robbed?

274
00:13:37.608 --> 00:13:38.901
I'm not the only person.

275
00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:43.322
You're the only one who filed a report.
but you waited an hour to call us.

276
00:13:43.405 --> 00:13:46.408
-Whoa. how did you know that?
-Time stamps don't lie. Harvey.

277
00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:50.120
You got hit right before midnight
and waited until 1:00 a.m. to call 911.

278
00:13:50.204 --> 00:13:52.957
Maybe there was something in this room
you didn't want us to know about?

279
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:55.501
[Stiles] Something to clean up
before we got here.

280
00:13:56.001 --> 00:14:00.714
I think you threw a private high-stakes
poker game here. and you got hit hard.

281
00:14:00.798 --> 00:14:03.133
I need to… call my lawyer.

282
00:14:03.217 --> 00:14:05.886
[Stiles] Uh-uh.
I'm not interested in your loser friends.

283
00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:07.513
I just wanna know about this girl.

284
00:14:08.389 --> 00:14:09.431
Who is she?

285
00:14:09.932 --> 00:14:13.435
[scoffs] That's Julia. She's been
a regular for a couple months now.

286
00:14:13.519 --> 00:14:15.354
[Stiles] Go ahead. tell me what happened.

287
00:14:15.437 --> 00:14:17.231
Look. we're back here playing.

288
00:14:17.314 --> 00:14:19.650
Then four dudes
dressed like 1930s gangsters

289
00:14:19.733 --> 00:14:21.527
bust into the room with guns.

290
00:14:21.610 --> 00:14:23.070
And they take your… your watch.

291
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:25.948
-Like I said in the report.
-All right. fuck it.

292
00:14:26.031 --> 00:14:29.326
-What about Julia? What does she do?
-They're waving guns in everybody's face.

293
00:14:29.410 --> 00:14:31.287
I go to reach for my piece.
which is licensed.

294
00:14:31.370 --> 00:14:33.372
Then she screams. "What are you doing?"

295
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:36.375
Then the big guy puts his gun to my head.

296
00:14:36.458 --> 00:14:39.128
You think she was warning him
that you had a gun?

297
00:14:40.212 --> 00:14:43.132
-You think she knew them?
-I think she set you up.

298
00:14:43.632 --> 00:14:45.009
Who was in charge?

299
00:14:45.634 --> 00:14:49.138
Uh. the smart one.
He said. uh. his intent was malicious.

300
00:14:49.221 --> 00:14:52.016
[chuckles] I don't know any Black people
who talk like that.

301
00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:54.894
How many Black people do you know. Harvey?

302
00:14:56.061 --> 00:14:59.648
-Uh-- Fair point.
-You want me to introduce you to some?

303
00:14:59.732 --> 00:15:03.611
Oh. Well. three of them were Black.
and one was. uh. Asian.

304
00:15:03.694 --> 00:15:07.072
Okay. um. is there anything else
that you remember

305
00:15:07.156 --> 00:15:09.241
that can help us get your watch back?

306
00:15:09.325 --> 00:15:12.369
Oh. The one wearing
the black-and-white wing tips.

307
00:15:12.453 --> 00:15:15.205
one of the Blacks.
he recognized the Patek.

308
00:15:15.289 --> 00:15:18.792
He grabs it. and he says.
"This mine's. cuh. It's my C-Day."

309
00:15:18.876 --> 00:15:20.836
Now. what the fuck is a "C-Day"?

310
00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:24.590
He said. "cuh" and "C-Day"?
You're absolutely sure?

311
00:15:24.673 --> 00:15:26.258
Yeah. why would I make that up?

312
00:15:26.342 --> 00:15:28.135
[ominous music playing]

313
00:15:28.218 --> 00:15:30.012
Yo. yo. Ika.

314
00:15:30.512 --> 00:15:33.057
Uce. what up?
Need your help with a suspect in my case.

315
00:15:33.140 --> 00:15:35.601
He's out here calling people "cuh."
talking about his C-Day.

316
00:15:35.684 --> 00:15:37.937
You know what I mean. Hit me back.

317
00:15:44.652 --> 00:15:46.862
[Choi] Yo. your breath
is clouding up the diamond.

318
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:48.572
-[Deon] Fuck you.
-Chill. man.

319
00:15:48.656 --> 00:15:51.367
Hey. this nigga on the news
talking about us.

320
00:15:51.450 --> 00:15:54.036
I know I've seen him.
but I don't know from where.

321
00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:56.705
Isaiah Stiles.

322
00:15:56.789 --> 00:15:59.541
The weed distro a couple years back.
Don't worry about him.

323
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:03.212
Soon as we offload the diamonds.
we're good. No diamonds. no Stiles.

324
00:16:03.295 --> 00:16:04.964
[tense music playing]

325
00:16:05.047 --> 00:16:06.465
There's one loose end. though.

326
00:16:07.508 --> 00:16:11.011
Deon keeps putting us on a razor's edge.

327
00:16:11.095 --> 00:16:14.014
[speaking indistinctly]

328
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:16.517
Deon got distracted. bro.
It could've been any of us.

329
00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:20.270
But it wasn't. First the watch.
and now this. That's strike two. man.

330
00:16:20.354 --> 00:16:22.940
Look. with Stiles
and the LAPD on the hunt.

331
00:16:23.023 --> 00:16:25.442
we can't afford any fuck-ups.
or it's a wrap on all of us.

332
00:16:25.526 --> 00:16:28.988
If you say you got me.
you can't let Deon slide on this one. bro.

333
00:16:32.157 --> 00:16:34.952
All right. look.
I'll tax his cut from the score.

334
00:16:35.035 --> 00:16:37.830
Maybe that'll get through
since bruh is so pressed for paper.

335
00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.749
Bet. I'm gonna go get us paid.

336
00:16:44.086 --> 00:16:45.713
What we looking like. Choi?

337
00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:49.091
Call these bitches Sydney Sweeney.
'cause they all-natural.

338
00:16:49.758 --> 00:16:52.344
No serial numbers.
Cleaner than Marie Kondo.

339
00:16:52.428 --> 00:16:55.973
Oh shit. we about to be lit.

340
00:16:56.056 --> 00:16:58.475
[Deon laughs]

341
00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:04.106
They didn't take anything at all.

342
00:17:04.189 --> 00:17:05.983
Every diamond. ruby. emerald.

343
00:17:06.066 --> 00:17:08.360
everything in our inventory
is accounted for.

344
00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:09.903
See for yourself.

345
00:17:10.404 --> 00:17:13.115
[tense music playing]

346
00:17:13.198 --> 00:17:18.454
You want me to believe three masked.
armed men broke into your stores.

347
00:17:18.537 --> 00:17:24.043
blew up the fucking walls. killed two men.
but left without a damn thing?

348
00:17:24.752 --> 00:17:26.837
Whatever you're hiding. I'm gonna find it.

349
00:17:26.920 --> 00:17:30.632
So I'm asking you. last time now.
what did they steal?

350
00:17:32.092 --> 00:17:35.596
-If we could tell you--
-Nothing. They stole nothing at all.

351
00:17:36.930 --> 00:17:38.891
[door opens]

352
00:17:38.974 --> 00:17:39.975
They're lying.

353
00:17:40.059 --> 00:17:42.061
[music fades]

354
00:17:42.895 --> 00:17:45.189
Yeah. I agree. But who the hell are you?

355
00:17:45.272 --> 00:17:46.648
Dave Cerullo.

356
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:50.861
Just transferred here.
16 years' Grand Larceny/Major Case. NYPD.

357
00:17:50.944 --> 00:17:54.364
Captain Sealey assigned me
to your robbery crew task force.

358
00:17:54.448 --> 00:17:57.117
Cerullo. why do you think they're lying?

359
00:17:57.201 --> 00:18:01.205
As soon as you applied pressure.
she stopped him from squealing.

360
00:18:01.830 --> 00:18:03.540
She's the one with the cojones.

361
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:06.668
I think they were afraid. And not of us.

362
00:18:07.294 --> 00:18:10.589
Detective 1. Jamel Brinkley.
Nice to meet you. sir.

363
00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:13.509
Nope.

364
00:18:15.761 --> 00:18:16.929
[door opens]

365
00:18:17.012 --> 00:18:21.016
-You wanted a team. I gave you a team.
-Ah-ah. No. No.

366
00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:24.269
I am not babysitting that kid. Jimmy.

367
00:18:24.353 --> 00:18:27.564
That "kid" has studied
every case you've ever closed.

368
00:18:27.648 --> 00:18:28.857
He's a fan of yours.

369
00:18:28.941 --> 00:18:30.609
Golden Retrievers like everybody.

370
00:18:32.444 --> 00:18:35.906
I know this is the first time
since Manny Shaw

371
00:18:35.989 --> 00:18:37.950
that you've been assigned a trainee.

372
00:18:38.033 --> 00:18:40.744
-[knocking on door]
-Sorry to interrupt.

373
00:18:40.828 --> 00:18:42.871
I was gonna tell you
before you left the room

374
00:18:42.955 --> 00:18:45.707
that in my experience.
stores like that. back-to-back.

375
00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:47.960
without consistent inventory.

376
00:18:48.043 --> 00:18:50.671
usually fronts.
operated by organized crime.

377
00:18:50.754 --> 00:18:53.423
I did some checking. made a call.

378
00:18:53.507 --> 00:18:56.343
On paper. the Petris own those stores.

379
00:18:56.426 --> 00:19:01.098
But their checks trace back to a company
owned by two Persian gangsters.

380
00:19:01.181 --> 00:19:02.558
Farid and Amin.

381
00:19:02.641 --> 00:19:05.727
Hope it's okay
I sent the uniform out to bring them in.

382
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.271
Goddamn right it's okay.

383
00:19:07.354 --> 00:19:09.314
So what if we're the real owners?

384
00:19:09.398 --> 00:19:10.607
That's not a crime.

385
00:19:10.691 --> 00:19:13.485
The Petris earn a percentage
for their trouble.

386
00:19:13.569 --> 00:19:18.240
You call threatening them.
their kids. their lives. a percentage?

387
00:19:18.323 --> 00:19:21.785
Like they said. nothing was stolen. okay?

388
00:19:21.869 --> 00:19:25.706
Maybe you don't wanna cooperate
because you were involved in the robbery.

389
00:19:25.789 --> 00:19:27.457
[Farid chuckles]

390
00:19:27.541 --> 00:19:30.419
We can charge you
with conspiracy to murder

391
00:19:30.502 --> 00:19:32.921
for the dead officer and guard.
What is that. Cerullo?

392
00:19:33.005 --> 00:19:34.506
25 to life. Lieutenant.

393
00:19:34.590 --> 00:19:36.300
[in Farsi] He is bullshitting.

394
00:19:36.383 --> 00:19:38.343
-[in English] You… You can't.
-[Stiles] Watch me.

395
00:19:38.427 --> 00:19:40.971
[Farid in Farsi] Be quiet.
They're bluffing.

396
00:19:42.472 --> 00:19:44.683
[in English] Amin. if I were you.

397
00:19:44.766 --> 00:19:46.476
I'd be wondering
why your partner over here

398
00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:49.188
is willing to let you go down
for two murders.

399
00:19:49.271 --> 00:19:50.939
[Farid scoffs]

400
00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:54.818
Each safe had a velvet burgundy bag
filled with untraceable diamonds.

401
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:56.445
-Headed to a black market auction.
-Amin!

402
00:19:56.528 --> 00:19:57.779
[in Farsi] Shut up!

403
00:19:57.863 --> 00:20:00.240
Admitting to trafficking stolen diamonds
will get us arrested anyway!

404
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:02.951
But it wouldn't be for murder.
This was your idea in the first place!

405
00:20:03.035 --> 00:20:04.161
I'm not going to jail for you!

406
00:20:04.244 --> 00:20:05.787
[in English] I wanna speak to my lawyer.

407
00:20:05.871 --> 00:20:09.833
Amin. three velvet bags of diamonds.
Who else knew about it?

408
00:20:09.917 --> 00:20:12.836
Lenn and Paulina are both sloppy. okay?

409
00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:15.422
Any of the people they hired
could have found what's in there.

410
00:20:15.505 --> 00:20:18.383
-Doesn't mean we fucking did it.
-[cell phone rings]

411
00:20:18.467 --> 00:20:19.968
Cerullo. take their statements.

412
00:20:20.677 --> 00:20:22.679
Ika. got something for me. uce?

413
00:20:22.763 --> 00:20:24.431
[Farid speaks in Farsi]

414
00:20:24.514 --> 00:20:27.851
[in English] Hey! Shut the fuck up!

415
00:20:28.352 --> 00:20:31.939
[Charlie] Thought you were
my best team. Coltrane. The fuck happened?

416
00:20:33.148 --> 00:20:36.777
The undercover security pulled a gun.
We had no choice but to shoot.

417
00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:38.820
I know it's messy.
but I have it under control.

418
00:20:38.904 --> 00:20:40.030
And?

419
00:20:40.989 --> 00:20:44.493
You gonna tell me about Deon and how
he's the reason that undercover pulled?

420
00:20:44.576 --> 00:20:46.828
[tense music playing]

421
00:20:46.912 --> 00:20:48.497
How you know about that?

422
00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:50.749
Bianca.

423
00:20:54.836 --> 00:20:57.256
Look. Deon will be heavily taxed
for his mistake.

424
00:20:57.339 --> 00:20:59.383
And that'll get his head in the game
for the next job.

425
00:20:59.466 --> 00:21:02.094
You can't guarantee
that Deon won't fuck up again.

426
00:21:02.177 --> 00:21:03.929
And if he gets caught. you get caught.

427
00:21:06.056 --> 00:21:07.224
You gonna handle him?

428
00:21:07.307 --> 00:21:09.434
Deon is under control.

429
00:21:09.518 --> 00:21:12.145
And he'll be more under control
once we get paid.

430
00:21:17.276 --> 00:21:21.321
As soon as those bodies hit the floor.
those diamonds became radioactive.

431
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:23.657
You wanna get paid?

432
00:21:23.740 --> 00:21:27.035
You and your crew are gonna do
the exchange with the buyer tomorrow.

433
00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:29.621
We never meet the client.

434
00:21:29.705 --> 00:21:31.957
You're never on the news. either.

435
00:21:54.646 --> 00:21:57.107
-[door opens. closes]
-[line dialing]

436
00:21:57.190 --> 00:21:59.985
Charlie. we still on for tomorrow?

437
00:22:00.068 --> 00:22:02.321
<i>My boys are gonna do the handoff.</i>
<i>but I need a favor.</i>

438
00:22:03.405 --> 00:22:06.533
[tense music continues]

439
00:22:06.616 --> 00:22:07.909
I need that one dead.

440
00:22:08.744 --> 00:22:12.289
The rest must leave alive and unharmed.

441
00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:13.874
<i>No mistakes. Farid.</i>

442
00:22:15.709 --> 00:22:16.752
I'll do it.

443
00:22:17.502 --> 00:22:18.879
For a price.

444
00:22:19.671 --> 00:22:21.298
As long as you get it done.

445
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:28.347
[tense music intensifies]

446
00:22:32.559 --> 00:22:33.769
[music fades]

447
00:22:33.852 --> 00:22:37.272
-Yo.
-[Stiles] Uh-oh. Here comes trouble.

448
00:22:37.356 --> 00:22:39.399
Look who came up in the world.

449
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:41.526
[laughing] Ika.

450
00:22:41.610 --> 00:22:42.778
My man.

451
00:22:44.237 --> 00:22:46.239
I got that thing you needed. uce.

452
00:22:49.076 --> 00:22:51.328
My nigga. Yeah.

453
00:22:52.162 --> 00:22:54.081
What's up with my perp. though?

454
00:22:55.332 --> 00:22:57.125
[exhales] Ooh.

455
00:22:57.834 --> 00:23:01.421
-Yeah. that's nice. right?
-I looked at the leads you sent me.

456
00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:03.965
Perp sounds affiliated
with our friends in blue.

457
00:23:04.049 --> 00:23:06.593
And I think you're onto something
with the gambling.

458
00:23:06.676 --> 00:23:07.636
How so?

459
00:23:08.887 --> 00:23:10.430
[Ika clears throat]

460
00:23:12.224 --> 00:23:15.560
I'm working on a major gang injunction
against a specific set.

461
00:23:15.644 --> 00:23:19.314
Target's a high-level member
running a major gambling operation.

462
00:23:19.398 --> 00:23:20.357
Baby Plus One.

463
00:23:22.818 --> 00:23:26.113
You think that my perp placed a bet
on Baby Plus One's books?

464
00:23:26.196 --> 00:23:29.408
-Biggest blue bookie out right now.
-Okay.

465
00:23:31.701 --> 00:23:33.662
Took me a long fucking time.

466
00:23:34.913 --> 00:23:37.290
but I flipped his right-hand man.
TyTy. as a CI.

467
00:23:38.875 --> 00:23:40.836
So it's possible that this TyTy.

468
00:23:40.919 --> 00:23:43.839
he knows my perp directly.
and he can ID him?

469
00:23:43.922 --> 00:23:45.173
Yeah.

470
00:23:45.257 --> 00:23:48.385
Look. I can bring him in.
You can take his statement.

471
00:23:49.177 --> 00:23:52.889
-Should take me a few days. though.
-No. I need to talk to your snitch today.

472
00:23:52.973 --> 00:23:55.183
TyTy's way too important
to my gang injunction.

473
00:23:55.767 --> 00:23:57.686
It's just a few days.

474
00:23:58.770 --> 00:24:00.856
[cell phone buzzes]

475
00:24:03.900 --> 00:24:05.735
Looks like you got shit to do
in the meantime.

476
00:24:06.945 --> 00:24:09.948
[hip-hop music playing over car stereo]

477
00:24:14.327 --> 00:24:15.328
[music stops]

478
00:24:21.042 --> 00:24:21.960
[doorbell rings]

479
00:24:23.044 --> 00:24:25.297
[Amos] Well. lookie here.

480
00:24:25.380 --> 00:24:27.048
It's the police.

481
00:24:27.799 --> 00:24:30.760
-What's up. Grandpa?
-Noah! What's up. boy?

482
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:33.096
-[Noah] What's up?
-What's up?

483
00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.848
-Yeah!
-[Noah chuckles]

484
00:24:37.184 --> 00:24:38.894
Ain't this a surprise?

485
00:24:38.977 --> 00:24:40.479
<i>He </i>wanted to see you.

486
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:43.356
Smell like a burnt Black & Mild.

487
00:24:43.982 --> 00:24:45.984
[R&B music playing over stereo]

488
00:24:49.863 --> 00:24:52.741
Been a while. little man. How you doing?

489
00:24:52.824 --> 00:24:54.075
I'm okay. I guess.

490
00:24:54.159 --> 00:24:56.828
-Okay. You got a girl or two yet?
-[Noah chuckles]

491
00:24:56.912 --> 00:25:00.290
[Noah] Well. it's this one girl.
Her name's Jenae.

492
00:25:00.373 --> 00:25:02.167
She's in my geometry class.

493
00:25:03.001 --> 00:25:05.879
Okay. Tell me about her.
What does she look like?

494
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:07.672
She got them wavy baby hair?

495
00:25:07.756 --> 00:25:10.258
-She got the wavy baby hair.
-[Amos laughs]

496
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:11.843
-She's cute. funny.
-[cell phone rings]

497
00:25:11.927 --> 00:25:13.345
Hey. I gotta take this.

498
00:25:21.269 --> 00:25:22.103
Yo.

499
00:25:22.187 --> 00:25:24.731
[Cruz] <i>I got the address for the banger</i>
<i>you wanted me to look into.</i>

500
00:25:24.814 --> 00:25:27.108
<i>Tyrell Reynolds. aka TyTy.</i>

501
00:25:27.192 --> 00:25:29.528
<i>He's staying with his girlfriend Portia</i>
<i>while he's on parole.</i>

502
00:25:29.611 --> 00:25:31.321
<i>Not sure why they let him out.</i>

503
00:25:31.404 --> 00:25:34.407
<i>He's got multiple felonies.</i>
<i>including possession. grand theft. and…</i>

504
00:25:34.491 --> 00:25:36.743
<i>This one's fun.</i>
<i>Assault with a deadly weapon.</i>

505
00:25:37.369 --> 00:25:39.079
How'd you find TyTy again?

506
00:25:39.162 --> 00:25:42.874
<i>Got friends in the gang unit. Cruz.</i>
<i>Text me his mugshot and address.</i>

507
00:25:42.958 --> 00:25:44.417
<i>You got it.</i>

508
00:25:44.501 --> 00:25:46.253
I'll get TyTy to play ball.

509
00:25:47.003 --> 00:25:49.839
Dad thinks you tried to get me high
three years ago.

510
00:25:49.923 --> 00:25:52.759
Never told him it was me who found
a clip of your blunt at Christmas.

511
00:25:52.842 --> 00:25:54.886
And you didn't give it to me.

512
00:25:56.137 --> 00:25:59.391
-Why didn't you tell him?
-I don't snitch. little man.

513
00:25:59.933 --> 00:26:02.143
Let alone on my own grandson.

514
00:26:03.478 --> 00:26:04.312
Never.

515
00:26:04.396 --> 00:26:05.397
[chuckles]

516
00:26:08.191 --> 00:26:09.359
What's that?

517
00:26:10.277 --> 00:26:13.405
This is… what's left of the old days.

518
00:26:14.322 --> 00:26:16.366
I founded my own set. you know.

519
00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:21.037
Most of 'em are long gone.

520
00:26:21.621 --> 00:26:22.706
Dead or in jail.

521
00:26:24.541 --> 00:26:28.878
My man Rambo sent this to me
the week he got the chair.

522
00:26:32.841 --> 00:26:34.384
"Yo. Nightmare."

523
00:26:34.467 --> 00:26:36.845
"Nightmare." That's you?

524
00:26:37.429 --> 00:26:39.556
Noah. work came up.

525
00:26:39.639 --> 00:26:42.559
Gotta drop you back at home. We gotta go.

526
00:26:43.059 --> 00:26:43.935
Now.

527
00:26:44.436 --> 00:26:45.312
All right.

528
00:26:46.062 --> 00:26:47.188
Bye. Grandpa.

529
00:26:49.899 --> 00:26:50.734
[Amos] Hey. hold up.

530
00:26:50.817 --> 00:26:54.112
-When do I get to see my grandson again?
-[tense music playing]

531
00:26:54.195 --> 00:26:56.114
This was a one-time thing.

532
00:26:57.532 --> 00:27:00.076
Happy Thanksgiving. Amos.

533
00:27:08.376 --> 00:27:09.461
[music fades]

534
00:27:15.925 --> 00:27:17.135
[knocking on door]

535
00:27:18.553 --> 00:27:21.056
[unsettling music playing]

536
00:27:21.139 --> 00:27:24.142
-Fuck. man!
-Oh. whoa.

537
00:27:24.225 --> 00:27:26.102
Sit down. nigga. Give me this shit.

538
00:27:26.186 --> 00:27:27.562
[laughs]

539
00:27:27.646 --> 00:27:29.439
Carrying a firearm violates your parole

540
00:27:29.522 --> 00:27:32.984
and cooperation agreement
with a big Samoan friend of ours.

541
00:27:33.693 --> 00:27:35.570
But I'm feeling generous today.

542
00:27:36.196 --> 00:27:38.573
If you tell me what I need to know.

543
00:27:39.157 --> 00:27:41.618
-Nigga. don't you need a warrant?
-This is my warrant.

544
00:27:42.744 --> 00:27:43.953
Fuck!

545
00:27:44.037 --> 00:27:46.498
Man I'm looking for.
he's affiliated with your set.

546
00:27:46.581 --> 00:27:48.792
Likes playing big money.
I'm talking tens of Gs.

547
00:27:48.875 --> 00:27:52.295
Might be flexing a new Patek Philippe
or trying to get rid of one.

548
00:27:52.379 --> 00:27:54.881
Put money on Baby Plus One's books
about a week ago.

549
00:27:55.465 --> 00:27:57.509
Warriors beat the Clippers that day.

550
00:27:58.468 --> 00:28:01.513
-We got a little action on the Warriors.
-Okay.

551
00:28:01.596 --> 00:28:06.017
[exhales] Only one fool's stupid enough
to put big money on the Clippers.

552
00:28:06.518 --> 00:28:07.519
Deon.

553
00:28:08.812 --> 00:28:10.313
Dumbass nigga.

554
00:28:10.397 --> 00:28:12.357
Cuh needs some help for real.

555
00:28:13.817 --> 00:28:15.527
I ain't know his government.

556
00:28:16.903 --> 00:28:18.571
But I know where he stay.

557
00:28:20.031 --> 00:28:20.990
[Stiles] Okay.

558
00:28:22.534 --> 00:28:26.162
We don't usually do this shit.
Drop off directly to the buyer?

559
00:28:26.246 --> 00:28:29.999
We don't drop unplanned bodies either.
Shit can't happen again.

560
00:28:30.083 --> 00:28:31.084
Facts.

561
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:34.838
-How do you think he'll take it?
-Don't care.

562
00:28:38.091 --> 00:28:40.301
Hey. D. let me holla at you for a second.

563
00:28:42.303 --> 00:28:45.390
'Cause you slipped on the job.
we taxing your cut on these diamonds.

564
00:28:45.473 --> 00:28:47.726
What? Nah. nephew. Fuck out of here.

565
00:28:47.809 --> 00:28:50.186
You lost focus. D.
You almost got shot. bruh.

566
00:28:50.270 --> 00:28:51.479
You handled it. though.

567
00:28:52.355 --> 00:28:56.359
But this reprimanding bullshit.
this 'Trane. ain't it?

568
00:28:56.443 --> 00:28:58.528
Nah. it's all of us. Choi too.

569
00:28:59.237 --> 00:29:02.115
Now. we gonna follow protocol on this.
We owe that to each other.

570
00:29:02.198 --> 00:29:04.576
I don't owe nobody.
Especially not that nigga 'Trane.

571
00:29:04.659 --> 00:29:07.328
He weird as fuck.
I don't care if that is your boy.

572
00:29:07.412 --> 00:29:09.831
He don't pay me
the same respect he pay you.

573
00:29:10.331 --> 00:29:11.750
Hey. look. Unc.

574
00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:14.919
I'm gonna tell you this shit one time.
so I need you to hear me.

575
00:29:15.003 --> 00:29:17.338
You fuck up again. and you out.

576
00:29:17.422 --> 00:29:20.508
And that's <i>my </i>call. Not 'Trane.

577
00:29:20.592 --> 00:29:22.218
[tense music playing]

578
00:29:22.302 --> 00:29:23.678
[cocks gun]

579
00:29:27.932 --> 00:29:29.559
[Stiles] Gideon Deon Davis.

580
00:29:29.642 --> 00:29:32.353
Deon joined the neighborhood set.
racking up a long juvie record.

581
00:29:32.437 --> 00:29:35.190
-Then served in the Army.
-That explains his demolition expertise.

582
00:29:35.273 --> 00:29:37.776
Enlisted at 18 years old
through a diversion program. but--

583
00:29:37.859 --> 00:29:41.696
He got a big chicken dinner
for gambling three years in. Figures.

584
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:44.491
-I'm sorry. What does that mean?
-Bad conduct discharge. kid.

585
00:29:44.574 --> 00:29:46.618
Then Deon took a job at a nightclub.

586
00:29:47.452 --> 00:29:48.828
His nephew. Darren Stroman.

587
00:29:48.912 --> 00:29:53.833
happened to get arrested for manslaughter
and attempted robbery at that nightclub.

588
00:29:53.917 --> 00:29:56.044
Ah. so Stroman does a stint at Lancaster.

589
00:29:56.127 --> 00:29:58.296
-Couldn't prove Deon was involved.
-But of course he was.

590
00:29:58.379 --> 00:30:01.257
Probably. but Stroman kept his mouth shut.
did the time alone.

591
00:30:01.341 --> 00:30:03.218
Here's Deon's known associates.

592
00:30:03.301 --> 00:30:05.637
I remember Harvey said
there was one man in charge.

593
00:30:05.720 --> 00:30:08.348
Just like on the surveillance footage
from the three stores.

594
00:30:08.431 --> 00:30:10.016
One guy calling the shots.

595
00:30:10.099 --> 00:30:11.601
Now. my gut says that Deon and Stroman.

596
00:30:11.684 --> 00:30:13.520
they're on the board.
but they're just soldiers.

597
00:30:13.603 --> 00:30:16.648
Harvey mentioned there was an Asian guy.
I don't see an Asian guy up there.

598
00:30:17.315 --> 00:30:21.820
Deon's IG shows him hanging
with a Korean guy named Chris Choi.

599
00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:23.530
[Cerullo] Looks like
they grew up together.

600
00:30:23.613 --> 00:30:25.907
Oh! Choi's got a juvie record.

601
00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:28.326
[Brinkley] They were enlisted
around the same time.

602
00:30:28.409 --> 00:30:31.204
Choi worked reconnaissance.
And he's a sniper.

603
00:30:31.287 --> 00:30:34.415
Nah. hold up.
Look. we need a more concrete connection.

604
00:30:35.124 --> 00:30:37.919
I'mma holler at Sealey.
We'll call up the warden at Lancaster.

605
00:30:38.002 --> 00:30:39.587
find more background on Stroman.

606
00:30:39.671 --> 00:30:43.466
Because we have to find these guys
before they sell those diamonds.

607
00:30:43.550 --> 00:30:46.553
["The Edge" playing]

608
00:31:14.163 --> 00:31:16.124
[song ends]

609
00:31:17.667 --> 00:31:19.961
So. you're the motherfucker
all over the news. huh?

610
00:31:20.044 --> 00:31:21.546
[laughs]

611
00:31:21.629 --> 00:31:23.506
Would you like your product or no?

612
00:31:24.090 --> 00:31:25.425
First things first.

613
00:31:25.508 --> 00:31:26.467
[in Farsi] Pat him down.

614
00:31:27.552 --> 00:31:30.013
[in English] Fuck that. We give up ours.
You should too. cuh.

615
00:31:30.096 --> 00:31:33.808
You're the one who fucked up this job.
Think twice before telling us what to do.

616
00:31:33.892 --> 00:31:35.727
Hey. give up your piece. D.

617
00:31:39.606 --> 00:31:40.523
You too. Choi.

618
00:31:46.946 --> 00:31:51.034
Good. Now that we have that
out of the way. your payment.

619
00:31:51.117 --> 00:31:52.118
[in Farsi] Give it to him.

620
00:31:54.829 --> 00:31:56.873
[in English] Yeah. Your diamonds.

621
00:31:59.208 --> 00:32:00.376
[henchman] Got 'em.

622
00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:01.836
Good.

623
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:04.839
[ominous music playing]

624
00:32:06.049 --> 00:32:07.383
[gunshot]

625
00:32:07.467 --> 00:32:09.260
[intense music playing]

626
00:32:09.344 --> 00:32:11.054
[grunting]

627
00:32:13.306 --> 00:32:14.724
[gunshot]

628
00:32:19.062 --> 00:32:20.063
Fuckers.

629
00:32:21.564 --> 00:32:23.858
-Hey. hold this. cuzzo.
-Thank you.

630
00:32:24.776 --> 00:32:28.446
What the fuck? This motherfucker tried
to merk us and shorted us a mil. bruh.

631
00:32:31.449 --> 00:32:34.202
Cuh. cuh. cuh. if we light on bread.
we should sell the diamonds.

632
00:32:34.285 --> 00:32:37.121
Leave it. Cops will see this
and think it's a deal gone sideways.

633
00:32:38.581 --> 00:32:41.125
All right. y'all. let's go.
Stro. Yung. come on.

634
00:32:42.710 --> 00:32:44.712
[engine starts]

635
00:32:45.713 --> 00:32:47.715
[dramatic music playing]

636
00:32:53.554 --> 00:32:55.932
[helicopter blades whirring]

637
00:32:56.015 --> 00:32:59.686
Four bodies equals four robbers.
including one suspect. Farid.

638
00:32:59.769 --> 00:33:02.438
who had motive. and you already
questioned him with Cerullo.

639
00:33:02.522 --> 00:33:04.649
The velvet bags match Amin's description.

640
00:33:04.732 --> 00:33:07.694
We'll bring him in
to confirm the bags and diamonds.

641
00:33:07.777 --> 00:33:11.406
{\an8}Farid may have double-crossed Amin.
but looking at the position of the bodies.

642
00:33:12.365 --> 00:33:15.660
{\an8}his men double-crossed him
and then each other.

643
00:33:15.743 --> 00:33:18.830
And these thugs had a sniper on payroll?

644
00:33:19.414 --> 00:33:20.873
It's too neat.

645
00:33:20.957 --> 00:33:23.876
These guys don't match Harvey's
perp description from the poker heist.

646
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:28.464
Perps from the jewelry store were
all wearing masks. and showing no skin.

647
00:33:28.548 --> 00:33:30.925
-Maybe it was a different group.
-It's the same guys.

648
00:33:31.009 --> 00:33:33.678
It's the same crew.
I know how they fucking operate.

649
00:33:33.761 --> 00:33:36.097
You can't just wrap this up
with a neat fucking bow.

650
00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:39.809
Sealey ordered us to close this case.
Look around. It's closed.

651
00:33:39.892 --> 00:33:43.021
[tense music playing]

652
00:33:43.104 --> 00:33:44.313
Gideon Davis.

653
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:48.359
-Deon is still a lead.
-So is Anna Kate Walachek.

654
00:33:48.943 --> 00:33:51.195
But this case is closed.

655
00:33:52.030 --> 00:33:53.281
You know Sealey won't care.

656
00:33:53.364 --> 00:33:55.450
So because this is over.
you stop being a cop?

657
00:33:57.869 --> 00:33:59.370
[Cruz] Motherfucker. you know what?

658
00:34:01.789 --> 00:34:02.790
[Cerullo] Come on.

659
00:34:13.593 --> 00:34:17.055
I know I'm new to this.
but I agree with you. Lieutenant.

660
00:34:17.638 --> 00:34:18.973
This feels off.

661
00:34:21.934 --> 00:34:24.187
I'd like to hear more
of what you're thinking.

662
00:34:25.271 --> 00:34:28.399
-You got plans for Thanksgiving?
-No.

663
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:30.109
You do now.

664
00:34:32.320 --> 00:34:33.905
For real?

665
00:34:33.988 --> 00:34:36.616
[ominous music playing]

666
00:34:36.699 --> 00:34:39.202
[Coltrane] Farid tried to kill us
and was short a million dollars.

667
00:34:39.285 --> 00:34:42.163
We put Farid down.
and his boys are done too.

668
00:34:43.539 --> 00:34:45.416
<i>I left the diamonds</i>
<i>and the guns with the bodies.</i>

669
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:47.919
all wrapped up in a nice red bow for LAPD.

670
00:34:49.087 --> 00:34:50.421
No loose ends.

671
00:34:50.505 --> 00:34:51.672
<i>Talk to you later.</i>

672
00:34:53.508 --> 00:34:55.176
[doorbell rings]

673
00:34:57.595 --> 00:35:00.681
What are you doing here?
I thought you were going to St. Bart's.

674
00:35:00.765 --> 00:35:03.309
I thought you understood
you had to leave after the jewelry store.

675
00:35:03.976 --> 00:35:07.271
Imagine my surprise
when I find out you were at LAPD.

676
00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:09.732
They ran your prints. Anna Kate.

677
00:35:14.487 --> 00:35:18.699
Don't think I've seen your place yet.
You mind if I come in?

678
00:35:20.284 --> 00:35:21.202
[music fades]

679
00:35:24.122 --> 00:35:27.166
-[upbeat music playing]
-[Sealey] Mm! Smells good in here. gents.

680
00:35:27.250 --> 00:35:29.127
Ha. ha!

681
00:35:29.210 --> 00:35:31.921
Wait a minute. Is that government cheese?

682
00:35:32.004 --> 00:35:33.714
My secret ingredient.

683
00:35:33.798 --> 00:35:36.217
-Ika from gang unit hooked me up.
-[scoffs]

684
00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:37.927
I always liked Ika.

685
00:35:38.427 --> 00:35:41.097
-Till now.
-[Stiles laughs]

686
00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:42.974
Come on. Jimmy. No. get off the stove.

687
00:35:43.057 --> 00:35:45.810
You need to put
some neck bone stock up in there.

688
00:35:46.769 --> 00:35:48.563
Warden Knight up in Lancaster
called me back.

689
00:35:48.646 --> 00:35:51.482
He's in town for the holiday.
and he's willing to meet you downtown.

690
00:35:51.566 --> 00:35:56.696
But… you don't need to go now. right?
The jewelry heist was solved last night.

691
00:35:56.779 --> 00:35:58.698
I could ask him a few questions.

692
00:35:58.781 --> 00:36:02.368
-[indistinct chatter]
-[upbeat R&B music playing over stereo]

693
00:36:02.451 --> 00:36:03.703
Nah. it can wait.

694
00:36:04.745 --> 00:36:07.248
Noah. give me the pan. Come on.

695
00:36:07.331 --> 00:36:09.542
Thanksgiving is not the holiday
to try to go healthy.

696
00:36:09.625 --> 00:36:11.043
Jimmy. you can cook next year.

697
00:36:11.127 --> 00:36:14.797
Mm! Ebony put
her fucking foot in these. cuh.

698
00:36:14.881 --> 00:36:17.967
I need to find one like her.
Fine as hell and can cook too? Shit.

699
00:36:18.050 --> 00:36:20.678
Bruh. you already got two women.
How many more you need?

700
00:36:20.761 --> 00:36:24.056
-Man-- You're right. You're right.
-See. Choi ain't even got one.

701
00:36:24.140 --> 00:36:25.474
-Man.
-[Deon] Ahh!

702
00:36:25.558 --> 00:36:27.560
It's cool. man. Just playing.

703
00:36:27.643 --> 00:36:29.979
Hey. man. So. when's our next job?

704
00:36:30.062 --> 00:36:32.023
I'm telling y'all
we should flock a superyacht.

705
00:36:32.106 --> 00:36:33.566
That shit ain't never been done.

706
00:36:33.649 --> 00:36:36.277
[Stro] Bruh. the closest you been
to the ocean is the Red Lobster

707
00:36:36.360 --> 00:36:38.070
in Inglewood off Century.

708
00:36:38.154 --> 00:36:39.989
[Charlie] Happy Thanksgiving. 'Trane.

709
00:36:40.072 --> 00:36:42.617
-[Coltrane] Happy Thanksgiving.
-[Charlie] Hey.

710
00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:45.578
You guys remember Charlotte?
Ebony's sister.

711
00:36:45.661 --> 00:36:47.872
I see looks run in the family.

712
00:36:47.955 --> 00:36:51.667
-[Deon] What's up?
-What y'all talking about? Mm?

713
00:36:52.168 --> 00:36:54.587
-Y'all going on a yacht?
-Just a little boys' trip.

714
00:36:54.670 --> 00:36:57.632
Ah. so I guess I'm not invited. Mm?

715
00:36:57.715 --> 00:36:59.050
You here with anybody?

716
00:37:00.301 --> 00:37:02.136
Can I talk to you for a second?

717
00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:04.263
Yeah. I'll be back. y'all.

